<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="497" pageId="3" pageNumber="496" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1948,2009]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,788]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="497" pageId="3" pageNumber="496">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1948,1973]" pageId="3" pageNumber="496">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species differs from the other 
<emphasis box="[667,751,1949,1973]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="496">Ashima</emphasis>
species by having the arista both with dorsal and ventral long branches and with apical expansion; however, it is slightly similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Toda" authorityName="Chen &amp; Toda" box="[933,1205,1984,2009]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tanabei">
<emphasis box="[933,1045,1985,2009]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="496">P. tanabei</emphasis>
Chen &amp; Toda
</taxonomicName>
in Chen 
<emphasis box="[1308,1365,1985,2009]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="496">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[1380,1436,1984,2008]" pageId="3" pageNumber="496" value="2005.0">2005</number>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[217,287,151,175]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[302,411,152,176]" name="Myanmar" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[475,578,151,175]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
in the aedeagus bearing prickly sclerites and numerous, small triangular processes (in 
<taxonomicName box="[303,415,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tanabei">
<emphasis box="[303,317,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[331,415,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">tanabei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: aedeagal median rod apically hooked, somewhat like anchor).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="497" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Description.</emphasis>
Frons brownish, with thick and dense interfrontal setae. Pedicel and first flagellomere yellowish. Face brown, with yellowish white patches on lower corners. Clypeus medially white, laterally black. Thorax and scutellum orange brown. Legs yellow, with neither submedial, dark spots on femora nor dark rings on tibiae; fifth tarsomere of foreleg with long seta apically (see 
<figureCitation box="[716,780,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="1.[151,263,1702,1725]" captionTargetBox="[187,1395,742,1651]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,724,1679]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Phortica (Allophortica) chingolaensis Chen &amp; Máca, sp. nov., male terminalia: 1. Epandrium (epand) and cercus (cerc) (lateral view); 2. surstylus (ventral view); 3. hypandrium (hypd), paramere (pm), gonopods (gon), aedeagal median rod (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (lateral view) (all scale lines = 0.1 mm through this paper)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282315/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">
Fig. 
<number box="[770,780,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="497" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cao" box="[845,1031,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="497" refString="Cao, H. L., Wang, X. L., Gao, J. J., Prigent, S. R., Watabe, H., Zhang, Y. P. &amp; Chen, H. W. (2011) Phylogeny of the African and Asian Phortica (Drosophilidae) deduced from nuclear and mitochondrial gene sequences. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 61, 677 - 685." type="journal article" year="2011">
Cao 
<emphasis box="[900,959,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[975,1031,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="497" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Abdominal third to fifth sternites broadened, shorter than wide, with several long setae laterally; sixth sternite without long setae laterally. Male terminalia: Surstylus with several setae, pubescence and ca. 
<number box="[828,856,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="497" value="10.0">10</number>
prensisetae on ventral margin to inner surface (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1658,1681]" captionTargetBox="[183,1417,873,1621]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,844,1637]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 10. Phortica (Ashima) mediarista Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia: 8. Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); 9. surstylus (inner view); 10. hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282317/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,165,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="497" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Paramere weakly sclerotized and smooth apically, with 
<number box="[854,868,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="497" value="2.0">2</number>
sensilla subbasally (
<figureCitation box="[1117,1202,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1658,1681]" captionTargetBox="[183,1417,873,1621]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,844,1637]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 10. Phortica (Ashima) mediarista Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia: 8. Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); 9. surstylus (inner view); 10. hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282317/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">
Fig. 
<number box="[1174,1202,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="497" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aegeagus lacking median rod (
<figureCitation box="[293,373,476,500]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1658,1681]" captionTargetBox="[183,1417,873,1621]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,844,1637]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 10. Phortica (Ashima) mediarista Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia: 8. Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); 9. surstylus (inner view); 10. hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282317/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">
Fig. 
<number box="[345,373,476,500]" pageId="4" pageNumber="497" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
